commit.message:
Add InspirationSet model and migrate to dynamic data

Introduces the InspirationSet model and migration in Prisma, updates seed data to include inspiration sets, and refactors frontend components to fetch categories, products, and inspiration sets from the database instead of static data. Removes unused generated Prisma files and updates .gitignore to exclude the entire /src/generated directory. Adds Prisma generate to postinstall and configures Prisma seed in package.json.

Add override for @auth/core to version 0.41.1

Added an 'overrides' section in package.json to enforce @auth/core version 0.41.1. This ensures consistent dependency resolution and addresses potential issues with mismatched versions in the project.

Update next-auth to v5 and fix cart item route params

Upgraded next-auth to version 5.0.0-beta.30 and added nodemailer as a dependency. Refactored cart item PATCH and DELETE API routes to handle async params and fixed usage of id extraction. Removed unnecessary ts-expect-error comment in auth session callback.

Update logo image sizing in Footer and Nav

Adjusted the Peak Blooms logo image dimensions and styling in both Footer and Nav components for improved appearance and consistency. Added custom height and width classes, and set eager loading for the Nav logo.

Add Prisma seed script and update DB integration

Introduced prisma/seed.ts for seeding the database and updated prisma.config.ts for new Prisma configuration. Refactored FeaturedCollections and FeaturedProducts components to fetch data from the database instead of static sources. Updated db.ts for new Prisma client usage. Added relevant dependencies for PostgreSQL and Prisma in package.json.

Add Prisma database, NextAuth, and API endpoints

Introduced Prisma ORM with full schema and migrations, NextAuth.js authentication with Resend email integration, and REST API routes for products, categories, user profiles, shopping cart, and orders. Added supporting documentation, utility functions, and updated dependencies in package.json. Updated .gitignore and cleaned up TODO.md.

Add serif font and update branding elements

Introduces Playfair Display as a serif font for elegant headings and applies it to key components. Updates social media links in the footer to use actual Peak Blooms profiles. Adds a custom logo image to the navigation bar, improves image loading with responsive sizes, and refines some text and layout details for consistency.

Update navigation links and color variables

Replaces 'About' and 'Contact' links with 'Collections' in the navigation, updates associated icons, and adjusts CSS color variables for primary and secondary elements. Also refines NavLink button hover styles for improved UI consistency.

Update site metadata for branding

Changed the site title and description in metadata to reflect Peak Blooms branding and provide a more descriptive summary for florist businesses.

Add inspiration sets feature and navigation

Introduces 'Inspirational Sets' with new pages for listing and viewing details of curated flower arrangements. Adds FeaturedInspiration component, AddToCartButton, and updates navigation to include Inspiration. Removes FeaturedCategories and updates the home page to showcase inspirational sets.

Add footer and featured categories components

Introduces a new Footer component and integrates it into the main layout. Adds a FeaturedCategories component for displaying curated flower collections. Updates FeaturedProducts subtitles for brevity and expands icon support with social media icons. Documents the decision to use a single light theme in the style guide.

Refactor to use rounded-xs for card and button corners

Introduces a new .rounded-xs utility for extra-small border radius in globals.css and updates all relevant components (FeaturedProducts, FeaturedCollections, and button variants) to use rounded-xs instead of rounded-sm/rounded-lg. Renames FeaturedCategories to FeaturedCollections and updates references and content accordingly for consistency with site terminology.

Add FeaturedProducts component and images

Introduces a new FeaturedProducts component displaying handpicked products with images and links. Updates the home page to use this component and adds four product images to the public directory.

Add featured categories section and images

Introduces a new FeaturedCategories component with three curated flower categories and associated images. Removes unused SVG files, updates the home page to display featured categories, and adds an ArrowRight icon to the UI icons module.

Refactor accent color usage to primary/secondary

Replaces 'accent' color variables and classes with 'primary' and 'secondary' throughout global styles and components. Updates Hero component to accept a ReactNode for CTA, allowing more flexible button rendering. This improves color consistency and simplifies theme management.

Add Hero component and gradient styles

Introduces a reusable Hero component for the site landing section, including a new radial gradient background utility and related CSS variables. Updates the home page to use the Hero component and adds a flower icon to the UI icon set.

Refactor UI controls to use shared Button component

Replaced custom and native button/link elements with the shared Button primitive across navigation and main page components for consistent styling and accessibility. Updated documentation to enforce Button usage for all interactive controls. Simplified button implementation and removed unused icon props. Minor style guide and CSS cleanup.

Add centralized icon system and integrate across UI

Introduces a new icons helper file re-exporting lucide-react icons with consistent sizing. Updates navigation, buttons, and CTA links to use these icons for improved affordance and visual hierarchy. Enhances accessibility and maintains a clean, modern aesthetic as documented in the style guide.

Add navigation bar and improve homepage layout

Introduces a responsive navigation bar with links and active state highlighting via new Nav and NavLink components. Updates layout.tsx to include the navigation and refactors page.tsx to enhance the homepage with a welcome section and call-to-action buttons. Cleans up README by removing extra documentation and deployment instructions.

Add documentation and update project overview

Added functional requirements and style guide documents to the docs directory. Updated README with project details, features, and tech stack. Modified next.config.ts to disable devIndicators. Simplified the home page by removing template content and placeholder UI.
